**Static data arrays defined inside component bodies** — the biggest offender. These objects are recreated on every render:

`src/components/Layout.tsx:11`
```tsx
// Before: recreated on every Navbar render
export function Navbar() {
  const navLinks = ["Home", "Cari Tukang", ...];
```

`src/components/Sections.tsx:4` and `:43`
```tsx
// Before: recreated on every render
export function Categories() {
  const categories = [{ title: "Tukang Bangunan", icon: Hammer, ... }];
```

`src/components/Workers.tsx:5`
```tsx
// Before: recreated on every render  
export function TopWorkers() {
  const workers = [{ id: 1, name: "Budi Santoso", ... }];
```

**Fix — hoist static data above the component:**
```tsx
// After: defined once, never reallocated
const NAV_LINKS = ["Home", "Cari Tukang", "Kategori", "Cara Kerja", "Testimoni", "Blog"];

const CATEGORIES = [
  { title: "Tukang Bangunan", icon: Hammer, color: "text-amber-700" },
  // ...
];

export function Navbar() { /* uses NAV_LINKS */ }
export function Categories() { /* uses CATEGORIES */ }
```

**Precomputed href slugs** — `link.toLowerCase().replace(" ", "-")` runs in the render loop for both desktop and mobile nav on every state change (`isOpen` toggle):

```tsx
// Before (computed twice per render per link):
href={`#${link.toLowerCase().replace(" ", "-")}`}

// After (precomputed once):
const NAV_LINKS = [
  { label: "Home", slug: "home" },
  { label: "Cari Tukang", slug: "cari-tukang" },
  // ...
];
// href={`#${link.slug}`}
```

---

**Worker images lack lazy loading.** The horizontal scroll container in `Workers.tsx` loads all 5 images eagerly — images 3–5 are off-screen on mobile:

```tsx
// Before:
<img src={worker.img} alt={worker.name} className="w-full h-full object-cover ..." />

// After:
<img
  src={worker.img}
  alt={worker.name}
  loading="lazy"
  decoding="async"
  width={300}
  height={192}
  className="w-full h-full object-cover ..."
/>
```

Same applies to the CTA phone mockup image (`src/components/CTA.tsx`):
```tsx
<img
  src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508214751196-bfdcf20eb432?w=300&h=300&fit=crop"
  loading="lazy"
  decoding="async"
  className="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-60 mix-blend-multiply"
/>
```

**Below-fold sections can be code-split.** `Categories`, `HowItWorks`, `TopWorkers`, `Features`, and `CTASection` are all below the fold. They could be lazy-loaded to reduce initial bundle:

```tsx
// src/App.tsx
import { lazy, Suspense } from "react";
import { Hero } from "./components/Hero";
import { Navbar, Footer } from "./components/Layout";

const Categories = lazy(() => import("./components/Sections").then(m => ({ default: m.Categories })));
const TopWorkers = lazy(() => import("./components/Workers").then(m => ({ default: m.TopWorkers })));
// etc.

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-white font-sans ...">
      <Navbar />
      <main>
        <Hero />
        <Suspense fallback={null}>
          <Categories />
          <TopWorkers />
          {/* ... */}
        </Suspense>
      </main>
      <Footer />
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

**Infinite animations run off-screen.** The floating `y` animations in `Hero.tsx` and `CTA.tsx` use `repeat: Infinity` and run continuously even after the element scrolls out of viewport, wasting GPU/compositor resources:

```tsx
// Hero.tsx — runs forever regardless of visibility
animate={{ y: [0, -12, 0] }}
transition={{ duration: 4.5, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
```

**Fix — pause when off-screen using `useInView`:**
```tsx
import { useInView } from "motion/react";
import { useRef } from "react";

function FloatingCard({ children, yRange, duration }) {
  const ref = useRef(null);
  const isInView = useInView(ref, { margin: "0px 0px -100px 0px" });

  return (
    <motion.div
      ref={ref}
      animate={isInView ? { y: yRange } : { y: 0 }}
      transition={isInView ? { duration, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" } : {}}
    >
      {children}
    </motion.div>
  );
}
```

**Social icon array in Footer** (`src/components/Layout.tsx`) creates a new array `[Facebook, Instagram, Youtube, Twitter]` inline on every render — minor but consistent with the hoisting fix above.

---

**Dead conditional in `HowItWorks`** — all branches resolve to the same class:

```tsx
// Before: always 'text-[#FF7315]' except idx===4
${idx === 3 || idx === 1 ? 'text-[#FF7315]' : idx === 4 ? 'text-amber-600' : 'text-[#FF7315]'}

// After: simplified
${idx === 4 ? 'text-amber-600' : 'text-[#FF7315]'}
```

**`Logo` renders `motion.div` for hover/tap on every mount** — `whileHover` and `whileTap` attach event listeners each time the Logo mounts (Navbar + Footer = 2 instances per page). This is minor, but if Logo is used more frequently, wrapping with `React.memo` prevents redundant subscriptions when parent re-renders:

```tsx
export const Logo = React.memo(function Logo({ className = "", textVisible = true }) {
  // ...
});
```

